node.text: @angelamorrismakeup this is EXACTLY what I’m getting at. These are the same ideas that people who want to take away our rights hold; these are the same ideas that people like Jordan Peterson hold; these are the ideas that incels hold: that women are “chaos” and sensuality and men are rationality and strength. So if they’re the root beliefs of patriarchy and wannabe sceptics, they’re not going to help women or anyone get free. And that’s why Peterson is so hostile to using people’s correct pronouns: because the existence of people of other genders destroys an ideology that depends on a male/female binary
So much to say about him and as a speaker, I have to censor because of how highly people regard him. Thanks for creating a space to discuss this approach.

I've been worrying about the influence of Tony Robbins' in women's empowerment spaces for years. (One of my essays -- see link in profile --- about TR is from 2016 and the other is from 2018.)⠀⠀
⠀⠀
To me, his teachings about femininity and masculinity appear to be pure patriarchy and misogyny..but all gussied up in the language of spirituality and self improvement. (He’s endorsed the books of Warren Farrell, who is often referred to as “the grandfather of the men’s rights movement”)
⠀⠀
This spiritualized gender binary is arguably the opposite of empowerment -- it reinforces beliefs that marginalize women -- yet so many women's empowerment coaches use the same ideas in their own work with women. Especially the ones who've trained with him. ⠀⠀
⠀⠀
I believe this is dangerous. Ideas like these arguably contribute to the marginalization of women and even to sexual harassment and abuse.⠀⠀
⠀⠀
Which I was not surprised about TR's apparent #metoo "misstep" last year or by the recent Buzzfeed articles.
⠀⠀
All this to say...if you work with women as a coach or healer and Tony Robbins is one of your influences, I invite you to reconsider his teachings and gender ideology through a feminist lens. ⠀⠀
⠀⠀
This is not a condemnation of you. It's an invitation. ⠀⠀ with so much love + justice,⠀⠀
Kelly⠀⠀
⠀⠀
links to my 2 essays in profile⠀⠀
⠀⠀
#metoo
Exactly why I unfollowed him last year.

@angelamorrismakeup I’m with you there. I keep those communities at arms length. We need to keep pushing to #BelieveSurvivors and educate each other on predatory behavior. Unfortunately the apologists tend to have something to gain by not shunning the person in my experience.
@crystalclearstorytelling you’re absolutely right.
@angelamorrismakeup you speak all the truth here

Thank you for saying this. I was a fan of his and did notice those things but figured it probably served his primary demographics (cis het folks with wealth) and took what worked for me while throwing out the rest that was cringy or didn’t apply to me. I got an update that he had a new video on YouTube and the title was something like “Not Afraid to Speak the Truth” or something where I immediately thought to myself “what happened?” I watched the 3-minute propaganda about what a great guy he is, with the montage and the music and bold typeface slamming onto the screen... then noticed that comments were disabled. I was VERY curious. With a google I saw that the Buzzfeed exposé on him had come out literally 45 minutes prior. Hyper-masculine narcissist who grew up with an abusive mom and worked his way up the rungs of power and influence with a hero image... I can’t say that I haven’t seen this before. It sucks we have to vet people who appear on the surface to do so much good because they’re motives and private behavior can be SO bad. People like this are getting smarter and more clever... they know exactly how to get the narcissistic supply they crave by curating a heroic image publicly, and get the abusive power and revenge they crave by being a monster privately
He's always given me an icky feeling but I just stayed quiet when other friends and peers raved. I'm so glad I found your work
@aka_wonder_woman I’ve never heard of him
@gabgriffreg ok, just checking, lol
@gabgriffreg is this the guy you were talking about?
Heck yes. I’m so glad people are taking about this 🙌🏼🙌🏼🙌🏼

I don’t relate well to male influencers ... but give me a woman who starts her own side hustle, raises kids, manages home and her health/fitness without ‘outsource everything’ as the answer, and you have my full attention!
@americanyogiindenhaag I appreciate it!
Hope you don’t mind that I share this/your work because this is important to me!
@jensalittleloopy totally agree. It's also completely lacking a trauma informed lens.
@fortitudeandflow yes, that too. So many things wrong with what he does.
@jensalittleloopy I 100% agree!

Tony Robbins is toxic on so many different levels. On top of this, his teachings ignore racial/gender/socioeconomic privilege and imply that if you fail to achieve your goals, it's simply because you don't believe the right things and lack the proper mindset. It's a horrible form of lucrative gaslighting disguised as personal development. So glad you're talking about this. ❤️

@fatlibink yes, this whole new age/spiritual “Divine Feminine/Divine Masculine” crap and how they must be balanced is really tiring especially when it’s so prevalent in so-called woke circles

it’s the ideology that’s the problem...even if Robbins disappeared, these ideas about masculinity and femininity continue to have a lot of traction in our culture. They’re in the mouths of MRAs AND the practices of ‘empowerment’ coaches

YES
HAVE THOUGHT THE SAME FOR A WHILE NOW AS WELLLL🔥🔥🔥

I am so, so grateful for this post and your commitment to raising awareness about Tony Robbins! So relieved to see I'm not the only one bothered by this. As a feminist who works with women I am so tired of hearing his ideas are so golden and they simply work hence they shouldn't be questioned if you want to be successful. Yes, they often work because of pervasive patriarchy. Not something I want to support with my actions, attention, heart or money.
So much to say about him and as a speaker, I have to censor because of how highly people regard him. Thanks for creating a space to discuss this approach.
